-- EU's Barnier to Unveil Plan to Harmonize Deposit-Insurance, Welt Reports
-- Patrick Donahue
-- 2010-07-12T05:58:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/eu-s-barnier-to-unveil-plan-to-harmonize-deposit-insurance-welt-reports.html

          
          
             Michel Barnier, the European Union’s
Financial Services Commissioner, will unveil plans to harmonize
the bloc’s deposit insurance as a way to ease market distortions
and protect savers, Die Welt reported.   
 Barnier’s plan includes establishing a deposit guarantee of
at least 100,000 euros in all 27 EU members states by the end of
2012, the newspaper reported.   
          
          


  


        